        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 5:24PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
West Blocton, or 8 miles north of Centreville, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Montevallo, Brent, Centreville, West Blocton, Wilton, Ashby,
Brierfield Ironworks Park, Hebron, Marvel, and Six Mile.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
